      },
      {
        "purpose": "english_translation",
        "value": "Products (shosanbutsu) — a long catalogue of Tosa's named local products printed WITHOUT quantities: papers, white/black sugar, eggs, tea, honey & strained honey, beeswax, bracken starch & rope, cypress rope, pine products (rope, knots, soot, resin), bayberry bark, paper-mulberry, thatch, woven mats (Tanba / Ōmi / Shichitō / Nakatsugi / tatami facings), ceramics, madder, agar & set-seaweed, eel & catfish, bamboo (large/medium/small) & inner bamboo, gallnut, cassia root & cinnamon, Bukuryō (Poria), dye plants (indigo leaf & stem, woad), cuttlefish bone, mulberry seed, and more. No per-item amounts are recorded (page list)."
